<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABIC - Finger Pointing Page - 9/8/96</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
<a href="/abic/top.map"><img src="/abic/images/top.gif" border="0" ALT="Americans Bac
k in Charge" ISMAP></a><p>
<P>
<P>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=4>Finger Pointing Page</FONT>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<H3>"The Mysterious Disappearance of the Metcalf Amendment:<BR>
<EM>A True Life Congressional Thriller</EM>. . .</H3>
<P>
<b>Chapter 2</b>
<P>
In the last chapter, we learned that ABIC had pointed the finger at the 67 House members who voted against the Metcalf Amendment -- an amendment offered by Rep. Jack Metcalf (R - WA) to stop the automatic pay increase scheduled for members of Congress.  The House adopted the amendment and under its provisions, Congress would receive no payraise this year.  (Note:  Congressional salaries in 1996 are $133,644 per year.)
<P>
We also learned that when the bill came out of the Senate committee, that the Metcalf amendment had <b><i>vanished without a trace</i></b>.  No one knew how it disappeared or whodunnit! ABIC pointed the finger at the prime suspects:
<P>
THE FIVE SENATORS ON THE SUBCOMMITTEE
<P>
<center>
<table BORDER=0 ROWS=3 COLUMNS=3 CELLSPACING=5 CELLPADDING=20>
<tr ALIGN=center>
<td><img src="/abic/images/ptf-729-jeff.gif" ALIGN="bottom"><br>
<center>James Jeffords<br>
R-Vermont</center></td>
<td></td>
<td><img src="/abic/images/ptf-729-kerr.gif" ALIGN="bottom"><br>
<center>Bob Kerrey<br>
D-Nebraska</center></td>
</tr>
<tr ALIGN=center>
<td><img src="/abic/images/ptf-729-camp.gif" ALIGN="bottom"><br>
<center>Ben Nighthorse Campbell<br>
R-Colorado</center></td>
<td VALIGN=top><img src="/abic/images/fin.gif"></td>
<td><img src="/abic/images/ptf-729-miku.gif" ALIGN="bottom"><br>
<center>Barbara Mikulski<br>
D-Maryland</td></center>
</tr ALIGN=center>
<tr>
<td ALIGN="right" VALIGN="middle"><img src="/abic/images/rt.gif"></td>
<td ALIGN="center"><img src="/abic/images/ptf-729-shel.gif"><br>
Richard Shelby<br>
R-Alabama<br>
Chairman</td>
<td ALIGN="left" VALIGN="middle"><img src="/abic/images/l.gif"></td>
</tr>
</table>
</center>
<P>
This week ABIC will be watching the Senate floor very carefully to see if the Metcalf Amendment makes a reappearance.  The Amendment was part of the Treasury, Postal Operations and General Government Appropriations bill, which may be voted on THIS WEEK!
<p>
Will some brave Senator stand up and reintroduce the Metcalf Amendment?  
<P>
If not, will the <STRONG>House stand firm</STRONG> in opposing the congressional payraise when the bill goes to conference?
<P>
Will we ever know <STRONG>what really happened</STRONG>?
<P>
<H3>Stay tuned to ABIC for the next chapter in the case of....<BR>
<STRONG><EM>"The Mysterious Disappearance of the Metcalf Amendment"</EM></STRONG></H3>

<P>
